00:40:17.370 --> 00:40:21.777
- Now Ecclesiastes and the
vision there is the one

00:40:23.370 --> 00:40:25.690
that you seem most to relate to.

00:40:25.690 --> 00:40:26.840
- Yeah, I do,

00:40:26.840 --> 00:40:31.620
I think the Book of
Ecclesiastes is maybe underread.

00:40:31.620 --> 00:40:33.640
It's a terrific little book.

00:40:33.640 --> 00:40:35.640
It claims to be written by Solomon,

00:40:35.640 --> 00:40:37.520
the wisest man ever to have lived.

00:40:37.520 --> 00:40:40.080
But in fact, it was written
hundreds of years later.

00:40:40.080 --> 00:40:43.960
Scholars who are linguistic
experts in Hebrew can date books

00:40:43.960 --> 00:40:45.640
on the basis of the style of the writing,

00:40:45.640 --> 00:40:47.800
It's pretty clear this is a later book,

00:40:47.800 --> 00:40:50.220
somebody claiming to
be Solomon, who wasn't.

00:40:50.220 --> 00:40:52.550
The point of the book can be found

00:40:52.550 --> 00:40:54.500
at the very beginning
where the author says,

00:40:54.500 --> 00:40:57.770
vanity of vanities, all is vanity.

00:40:57.770 --> 00:41:00.560
The word vanity is a Hebrew word, hevel,

00:41:00.560 --> 00:41:02.040
which means, it's something like

00:41:02.040 --> 00:41:03.840
the mist that's around for a little while

00:41:03.840 --> 00:41:05.940
and then burns off and it disappears.

00:41:05.940 --> 00:41:07.630
So, it means something that's transient,

00:41:07.630 --> 00:41:12.040
temporary, impermanent, and
that's what all of life is.

00:41:12.040 --> 00:41:13.770
This world goes on and on and on,

00:41:13.770 --> 00:41:14.700
nothing ever changes.

00:41:14.700 --> 00:41:16.110
There's nothing new under the sun,

00:41:16.110 --> 00:41:18.520
but we're here just for a little while.

00:41:18.520 --> 00:41:20.850
And so, what does one do with that?

00:41:20.850 --> 00:41:22.730
Well, the Book of
Ecclesiastes looks around

00:41:22.730 --> 00:41:25.360
and sees there's no justice.

00:41:25.360 --> 00:41:27.620
And he looks around and sees
we're not here for long,

00:41:27.620 --> 00:41:31.510
and his conclusion is
we should eat and drink,

00:41:31.510 --> 00:41:34.740
and enjoy our toil, and enjoy our spouse.

00:41:34.740 --> 00:41:37.160
He believes that you should
grab the simple pleasures

00:41:37.160 --> 00:41:39.430
in life for as long as you can

00:41:39.430 --> 00:41:41.610
because this life is all you have.

00:41:41.610 --> 00:41:43.060
There's no afterlife,

00:41:43.060 --> 00:41:45.160
this isn't a dress rehearsal
for something else.

00:41:45.160 --> 00:41:47.490
It's not a dry run, this is it.

00:41:47.490 --> 00:41:49.370
And so you should enjoy life

00:41:49.370 --> 00:41:52.960
for all it's worth while you can.

00:41:52.960 --> 00:41:57.923
- One of the solutions that
you discuss has appeared

00:41:59.960 --> 00:42:04.170
to have greater relevance in our time

00:42:04.170 --> 00:42:07.350
because of the way it
